# Arran DnD — UI Base Components

All shared UI primitives are in `client/src/components/ui/`. **Always use these — never redefine their patterns inline.**

## Available Components

### `AppPageHead` — page header
```vue
<AppPageHead>
  Page Title
  <template #actions>
    <!-- buttons go here -->
  </template>
</AppPageHead>
```

### `AppCard` — bordered card
```vue
<!-- Simple title -->
<AppCard title="Section Title">
  content
</AppCard>

<!-- Title with action buttons -->
<AppCard title="Section Title">
  <template #titleActions>
    <button class="btn ghost small">+ Add</button>
  </template>
  content
</AppCard>

<!-- Complex header (use manual .card-head in slot) -->
<AppCard>
  <div class="card-head">
    <h2>Custom header</h2>
    <button>...</button>
  </div>
  content
</AppCard>
```

### `AppBadge` — colored pill
Variants: `attaque` | `limitée` | `gratuite` | `info` | `pm` | `active`
```vue
<AppBadge variant="attaque">Attaque</AppBadge>
```

### `AppEmptyState` — feedback block
Variants: `loading` | `empty` (default) | `error`
```vue
<AppEmptyState variant="loading">Chargement…</AppEmptyState>
<AppEmptyState variant="error">
  <p>{{ error }}</p>
  <template #actions><button @click="retry">Réessayer</button></template>
</AppEmptyState>
```

### `AppIconBtn` — 40×40 icon button
Variants: `ghost` (default) | `primary` | `danger`
```vue
<AppIconBtn variant="primary" title="Add" @click="...">
  <Plus :size="18" />
</AppIconBtn>
```

## Rules
- Import from `../components/ui/ComponentName.vue`
- Do NOT re-create `.page-head`, `.card`, `.badge`, `.empty-state`, or `.icon-btn` patterns in scoped styles
- All icons via `lucide-vue-next` only (no other icon libraries)
